<P>
 In nonleague boys' soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 3, Santa Margarita 3 -- Capistrano Valley scored two goals 
in a 10-minute span of the second half to erase a two-goal deficit. Ryan 
Hawkins scored two goals and Nick Hannay added one for the Cougars (6-1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Seth George scored two goals and Miguel Godoy added one for Santa Margarita 
(5-0-1), ranked second. 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena 5, Rialto Eisenhower 1 -- Bret Taylor scored two goals to lead El 
Modena (2-1). Nick Purdom, Robbie Merchant and David Fisher each added one in 
the victory over Eisenhower (2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro 0, Mater Dei 0 -- Charger goalie Sean Taeger made eight saves. Paul 
Gerdis had four saves for Mater Dei. El Toro (1-3-1) did score a goal in the 
first half but the Chargers were offside and the tally was nullified. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 3, Long Beach Poly 0 -- Doug Holt scored the first goal for 
No. 1-ranked Fountain Valley 25 minutes into the game with an assist from Ryan 
Futagakin. Joey Vasquez scored the second goal and Joey Bove capped the scoring 
for Fountain Valley (4-0) on a penalty kick. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 1, Western 0 -- Aaron Olea scored off an assist by Gurineara Sinngh 
for Fullerton (1-0-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 3, La Quinta 2 -- Danny Arreguin's second-half penalty kick was the 
game-winner for visiting Kennedy (1-0-1). Arreguin had two goals. Leo Cituomen 
added another goal for Kennedy. Brendon Alves and Matt Siebert scored goals for 
La Quinta (0-3). 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 1, El Dorado 0 -- Jeff Ruesga scored with 10 minutes remaining to 
break a scoreless tie and give La Habra (3-0) the victory over El Dorado (2-1). 
Aaron Scott had four saves for La Habra and El Dorado's Mark Zubiate also had 
four saves. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 3, Santa Ana 1 -- Danny Califf, Victor Diaz and Lalo Rodriguez each 
scored goals for Orange (2-1-2). Jose Sorto had Santa Ana's only goal. 
</P>
<P>
 Santiago 2, Sonora 1 -- Adrian Robledo scored the winning goal with five 
minutes left to lead Santiago (4-0) past Sonora (2-1). Goalkeeper Alex Carranza 
had a save in the final two minutes to preserve the Cavaliers' victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna 4, Troy 3 -- Goalkeeper Jose Albarran blocked five shots in the last 
five minutes of the game for Savanna (2-0-1) to dash any hopes for Troy (0-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills 5, Loara 0 -- Sunny Hills goalkeepers Jeff Murphy and Miguel Pasos 
combined to post a shutout and hand Loara (2-1) its first loss. Davis Lee had 
two goals for the Lancers (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 St. Margaret's 2, Malibu Kilpatrick 0 -- Patrick Moss and James Harris each 
scored a goal to lead St. Margaret's (1-1). Teammate Jeremy Blumberg had 10 
saves. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia 1, Canyon 1 -- Bobby Reimbold scored a first-half goal for visiting 
Canyon (2-1-1). Valencia tied the score in the 55th minute. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Irvine girls' soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 1, Dana Hills 1 (Irvine wins shootout 3-2) -- Katie Roda scored a 
second-half goal to tie the score for tournament host Irvine (5-0). Irvine 
advanced on penalty kicks and will play Los Alamitos in the finals Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague girls' soccer: 
</P>
<P>
