<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARMIJO IN MAIN EVENT ON IRVINE CARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntington Beach welterweight John Armijo will headline tonight's fight card 
at the Irvine Marriott that begins at 7:30 p.m. Armijo (18-7, 11 knockouts), 
riding a four-bout winning streak, will face Gilbert Flores (24-13, 21 
knockouts) of Los Angeles in a 10-round fight. 
</P>
<P>
 Since returning from a one-year layoff, Armijo has victories over Rene 
Aredondo and Bazooka Limon. 
</P>
<P>
 The featured undercard bout is a six-rounder between Huntington Beach 
bantamweight Kid Dynamo (3-1-2) and Frankie Hanks (3-2) of El Monte. Tickets 
for the six-bout event are $25, $30 and $35 and go on sale at the Irvine 
Marriott at 9 a.m. today. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
