<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CALABASAS; IMPROVEMENTS TO BEGIN ON STUNT ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Stunt Road will be improved in the unincorporated area near the city of 
Calabasas, Los Angeles County officials said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The project, to be administered by the county Department of Public Works, 
includes construction of a corrugated steel pipe drainage ditch to replace an 
existing undersized ditch. 
</P>
<P>
 "By improving drainage to take the water runoff away, the road will be more 
stable," said Joel Bellman, press deputy for Supervisor Zev Yaroslavsky, who 
represents the area. 
</P>
<P>
 Bids for the project, approved last month by the Board of Supervisors, will be 
taken beginning Dec. 20. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting in February, 1995, the project should take 35 working days and be 
completed in March. Once work begins, traffic on Stunt Road may be reduced to 
one lane for both directions during daytime hours and be controlled by flag 
operators. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
