<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; 2 BODIES IDENTIFIED AS MISSING COUPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two bodies found in widely separated desert areas were identified Wednesday as 
those of a missing Lancaster couple, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The body of Carlos Guevara, 26, was found alongside 50th Street East near 
Palmdale Boulevard on Nov. 30 by patrolling sheriff's deputies, Los Angeles 
County Sheriff's Deputy Rich Erickson said. 
</P>
<P>
 The body of his wife, Delia Guevara, 26, was found the same day in the desert 
community of Yermo in San Bernardino County by someone walking a dog along 
Interstate 15, Erickson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said Carlos Guevara was shot several times, dumped in the 
Antelope Valley and set on fire. Authorities would not say how Delia Guevara 
was killed. 
</P>
<P>
 The Guevaras were reported missing Saturday by a friend who became concerned 
when neither of them showed up for work. The couple was last seen Nov. 29, 
Erickson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Delia worked as an assistant manager at a Palmdale fast-food restaurant and 
her husband worked at the Best Buy store near the Antelope Valley Mall, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 A murder investigation began when deputies -- acting on the missing person 
reports -- found a bullet lodged in a wall of the Guevaras' home in the 42000 
block of Alep Street, Erickson said. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple's maroon 1994 Pontiac Grand Am is still missing, Erickson said. 
JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</TEXT>
