<P>
CONSTRUCTION CRANE PLUNGES 28 STORIES, KILLS THREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three men were killed Wednesday afternoon when a crane being lowered from an 
unfinished hotel tower broke loose and fell 28 stories to the parking lot, 
dragging a second crane with it, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 When the accident occurred, construction was winding down on a high-rise 
addition to the Riverside Resort hotel and casino in this Colorado River gaming 
outpost near the borders of California, Arizona and Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
 A 320-foot free-standing crane was lowering another crane from the top of the 
hotel tower when "down they came," said Robert Leinbach, spokesman for the 
Clark County Fire Department. "The free-standing crane killed the three people. 
The top portion of the other crane is now embedded in the parking lot." 
</P>
<P>
 Two of the men were in separate cars when they were struck; the third was 
walking in the parking lot. 
