<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY IN BANKRUPTCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 THE KEY PLAYERS 
</P>
<P>
 Robert L. Citron: Resigned after 24 years as county treasurer-tax collector 
when his risky investment strategy forced Orange County government to file for 
Bankruptcy Court protection. 
</P>
<P>
 William G. Steiner: The county supervisor accused federal securities 
regulators of sitting idle when they might have rescued the county from having 
to file for bankruptcy protection. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas F. Riley: The former Marine brigadier general chairs the Orange County 
Board of Supervisors, which approved the historic bankruptcy decision. 
</P>
<P>
 Ernie Schneider: The county's chief administrative officer moved Citron aside 
and took control of the investment portfolio as supervisors debated whether to 
file bankruptcy. 
