<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: CERRITOS; CITY COUNCIL BOOSTS ITS TRAVEL ALLOWANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council, asserting that driving around on official business has 
become more costly, has increased its monthly car allowance. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members voted 4 to 1 to raise their stipend for gasoline, auto 
maintenance and insurance from $250 to $400 a month, the first increase since 
1986.  
</P>
<P>
 Mayor Pro Tem Grace Hu said she voted for the increase because traveling costs 
are higher for council members, who drive to meetings throughout the county. 
The higher stipend matches the amount paid to city department heads. Mayor Paul 
W. Bowlen voted against the measure. "I think (the car allowance) was 
sufficient the way it was," he said. JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
