<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; MARKET, BANK ROBBED WITHIN 10 MINUTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two armed robberies, at a grocery store and a bank, occurred just 10 minutes 
apart Wednesday evening in Thousand Oaks, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The first robbery occurred at 5:55 p.m. at the Vons market on Avenida de los 
Arboles, Ventura County sheriff's deputies said.A man carrying what appeared to 
be a toy gun took an unknown amount of money from the pharmacy counter, Sgt. 
Ray Nagel said. 
</P>
<P>
 The second robbery was at 6:05 p.m. at the Wells Fargo Bank branch at 140 E. 
Thousand Oaks Blvd. Two men displayed handguns and fled with an undisclosed 
amount of money, Nagel said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police apprehended a suspect in the grocery store robbery late Wednesday. Both 
robberies were still under investigation. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
