<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: POINT MUGU; HOSPITAL ESCAPEES FOUND NEAR BASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two patients at Camarillo State Hospital -- an 18-year-old man accused of 
attempted homicide and a 21-year-old woman -- were picked up near Point Mugu 
Navy base Wednesday morning after escaping overnight from the mental hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple apparently left the facility Tuesday night while other patients 
were having coffee and snacks after a service in the hospital's chapel. 
</P>
<P>
 "I guess the staff must have turned their back for a minute or something and 
they took off and jumped the fence," said hospital spokeswoman Lynette 
Castleman. "The staff immediately searched the area, but it was already dark." 
</P>
<P>
 A sheriff's helicopter and two police dogs were called to assist in the 
search, but the couple could not be found. 
</P>
<P>
 About 9 a.m. Wednesday, employees at Point Mugu spotted two people near the 
perimeter of the military base and became suspicious. The employees then 
learned of the missing patients and called the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Castleman said the 18-year-old man was committed to the hospital four months 
ago by a Ventura County judge. The teen-ager will undergo treatment at the 
hospital until he is declared competent to stand trial on a charge of attempted 
homicide. 
</P>
<P>
 Castleman declined to give his name or details of the crime, although she did 
say that according to a diagnosis he is developmentally disabled with mental 
problems. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
