<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles has its trendy bistros. Philadelphia has its steak sandwich. New 
York has the pizza. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County's culinary claim to fame may well be found at Knott's Berry 
Farm, home to famous fried chicken served plump and crispy with a basket of 
buttery biscuits, creamed corn, mashed potatoes and berry pie. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrons wait in line for half an hour or more to eat at the restaurant, which 
serves 1,000 chickens and 500 pies daily. 
</P>
<P>
 Knott's Berry Farm officials say the restaurant's busiest day was Mother's 
Day, 1982, when 8,400 meals were served. 
</P>
<P>
 The restaurant's popularity spawned a take-out window. Today 
</P>
<P>
 The Bowers Museum of Cultural Arts will be transformed into a silent movie 
hall today. 
</P>
<P>
 The museum will present five silent short films starring Mary Pickford. The 
legendary actress is considered one of the greatest silent film stars. 
</P>
<P>
 The films will be shown at 7:30 p.m., and they are included with the price of 
museum admission. 
</P>
<P>
 The museum is at 2002 N. Main St. in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 You can receive more information about the screening by calling (714) 
567-3600. 
</P>
