WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; PLANNING BOARD OKS HMO'S BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Camarillo Planning Commission has unanimously approved a health 
maintenance organization's plans to build a 19,120-square-foot medical building 
on the city's east side. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposal by Foundation Health Inc., set for a vacant three-acre parcel 
near Adolfo Road and Avenida Acaso, would allow the company to retain more 
family practice physicians and to centralize services for members, spokesman 
Kurt Davis said. 
</P>
<P>
