<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROP. 187 COVERAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As a devoted Times reader, I am disappointed in your biased publishing of 
mostly anti-187 articles and letters.In your Nov. 27 editorial of "Jail 
Overcrowding," you mention inmates will leave early due to insufficient space; 
you do not mention that 18% of California's inmates are illegal aliens. 
</P>
<P>
 While you focus on children of illegals being victims, you do not mention 
compromising the education of legal children by overcrowding classrooms 
particularly in low-income areas where we have gang problems and lower rates of 
graduation.  
</P>
<P>
 Latinos see 187 as racial discrimination. However, it is more a rebellion 
against classrooms becoming overcrowded, our streets becoming more dangerous, 
and putting our systems into chaos.  
</P>
<P>
 JANET RICHARDSON 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Beach 
</P>
