<P>
 Approval of Macy-Federated Merger Expected: The marriage of the once-fierce 
rivals, Macy & Co. and Federated Department Stores Inc., will bring to an end 
nearly three years in Chapter 11 bankruptcy for Macy.It will also form the 
nation's biggest department store chain, with more than 335 stores and annual 
sales exceeding $14 billion. Barring last-minute hitches, U.S. Bankruptcy Judge 
Burton R. Lifland will confirm the plan today. Federated will pay off more than 
$4 billion of Macy's debt and Macy will emerge from bankruptcy status later 
this month. 
